cast.text:
The Moon Tale of the Girl Who Lives on the Moon
Open Edition
Free mint

html.ogDescription: MOON TALEOnce upon a time there was a girl named Luna, with two long pigtails that always bounced merrily when she moved. Luna lived not on Earth, but on the Moon, in a cozy little house near the crater. She loved her life in the lunar expanse and explored the silvery plains and mysterious caves every day.Luna had an unusual ability - she could talk to the moon rabbits, little creatures with big eyes and fluffy tails. Together they had fun playing games, jumping over craters and picking moonflowers that glowed in the dark.One day, Luna learned that there was a girl named Fei Fei on Earth who missed her mom very much and baked moon gingerbread according to her grandmother's recipe. Luna decided to help Fei Fei and traveled to Earth. She used ancient moon pollen to create a star path between the Moon and Earth.Upon arriving on Earth, Luna met Fei Fei and her family. Together they baked moon gingerbread, which filled the house with warmth and memories of Fei Fei's mom. Luna told Fei Fei about her adventures on the moon and how important it is to remember and appreciate loved ones who are gone.Fei Fei was amazed by Luna's stories and decided that she wanted to visit Luna to see things for herself. Luna gladly invited her to visit.Thus began a friendship between the two girls, separated by millions of kilometers, but united by moon magic and the sincerity of their hearts. Luna returned to the moon, but promised Fei Fei that they would see each other again soon, and their friendship would be as eternal as the light of the moon in the night sky.Programs used :AI - QWen 2.5PhotomoshDa vinci resolveFantasy

html.ogDescription: Deep in an ancient forest, surrounded by centuries-old trees and mystical mist, stood a majestic tower. Inside it lived a girl named Ariel. She was known for her amazing gift - the ability to emit luminous auras of different colors that reflected her emotions and state of mind.Ariel wore a thin black veil that slightly covered her face, adding even more mystery. But despite this veil, her radiance was so bright that it shone through the fabric, illuminating everything around her.Ariel spent hours each day meditating and developing her abilities. She could change the colors of her aura depending on her mood: soft blue when she felt calm, bright green when she felt joy, deep purple when she was thinking.But the most amazing thing was that her aura could interact with the world around her. When she passed trees, their leaves would glow the same shades as her aura. The animals in the forest sensed her presence and came closer, attracted by the soft light.However, not everyone knew of this gift. Only a select few were able to see Ariel in her full glory.
